I'll guide you through the complete Salesforce and Slack integration setup for the Koa Cars assignment. Here's a structured approach:

Phase 1: Slack Sandbox Setup (Task 1)
Step 1: Join Slack Developer Program
Go to https://api.slack.com/developer-program
Click "Join the Program"
Fill out registration form with your email
Check email for confirmation and click "Activate Developer Account"
Sign in and accept Terms of Service
Step 2: Provision Slack Sandbox
In Slack Developer Dashboard, navigate to "Sandboxes"
Click "Provision Sandbox with event code"
Enter event code: SLACK360_AGENTFORCE
Name your sandbox (e.g., "Koa Cars Workspace")
Click "Provision Sandbox"
Wait for provisioning to complete (appears in Sandboxes list)
Click sandbox name and log in
Click "Launch in Slack"
Phase 2: Connect Salesforce and Slack (Task 2)
Step 1: Install Slack Connector in Salesforce
Sign in to your Salesforce trial org
Go to this URL (replace YOUR_INSTANCE with your Salesforce instance):
Select "Install for All Users"
Check "Yes, grant access to these third-party web sites"
Click "Install"
Wait for installation to complete
Step 2: Request Connection from Slack
In your Slack workspace, click your organization name in sidebar
Hover over "Tools & settings" → "Manage Salesforce Organizations"
Click "Get Started" or "Connect Salesforce Org"
Enter your Salesforce org URL (e.g., https://your-domain.develop.my.salesforce.com)
Toggle "Automatic account mapping" OFF
Click "Request Connection" → "OK"
Step 3: Approve Request in Salesforce
In Salesforce, click Setup (gear icon)
In Quick Find, search: "Slack"
Click "Manage Slack Connections"
Check the box to agree to terms
Click "Approve"
Step 4: Activate Connection in Slack
Back in Slack: Organization name → Tools & settings → Manage Salesforce Organizations
Under "Connection Status", click "View Details"
Click "Activate" button
In modal, click "Activate" again
Step 5: Add Users in Slack
In connected Salesforce org settings in Slack, select "Users" tab
Click "Add individually"
Search for your name
Select your user
Click "Grant Access to 1 Person"
Step 6: Sign In to Salesforce from Slack
In Slack, click your profile icon → Preferences
Select "Salesforce" tab
Click "Sign In"
Click "Continue to Salesforce"
Enter Username and Password → "Log In"
Click "Allow"
Verify "Connected" status appears
Phase 3: Explore Automotive Cloud Data (Preparation)
Before Creating Agent
In Salesforce, open App Launcher (9 dots icon)
Search and open: "Service Console for Automotive"
Click "Vehicles" tab
Select vehicle: "2021 Electra Motors Megavolt GT"
Review vehicle details
Click current owner: "Oldacres's Electra of Dallas"
Explore related lists:
Contacts (drivers)
Service Appointments (dates, status)
Work Orders (status, priority)
Familiarize yourself with record relationships
Phase 4: Create Agentforce Agent (Task 3)
Step 1: Enable and Create Agent
In Salesforce Setup, search: "Agentforce"
Click "Agents" under Agent Studio
Click "New Agent"
Select template: "Slack Customer Insights"
Click "Next"
Verify these topics are checked:
General FAQ
General CRM
General Slack
Create an Executive Brief in Slack
Configure agent:
Name: Koa Cars Agent
API Name: Koa_Cars_Agent
Description: (leave default)
Role: (leave default)
Company: Koa Cars is a modern automotive sales and service company that leverages Salesforce Automotive Cloud to manage its end-to-end customer, vehicle, and service operations.
Click "Next" → "Create"
Click "Activate"
If pop-up appears, click "Ignore & Activate"
Step 2: Explore General Slack Topic
In agent details, go to "Topics" tab
Click "General Slack" topic
Review "Topic's Actions" to see capabilities
Step 3: Connect Agent to Slack
In Agent details, click "Connections" subtab
Scroll to "Connections" section
Click "Add"
Configure:
Connection Type: API
Integration Name: Koa Cars Agent
Connected App: Select "Slack"
Click "Save"
Step 4: Grant Agent Access
Click "Agent Access" subtab
Add "System Administrator" profile
Save
Phase 5: Install Agent in Slack (Task 3 continued)
Step 1: Install from Slack Admin
In Slack, click workspace name → Tools & settings → Organization settings
In left sidebar: "Salesforce" → "Agentforce"
Find "Koa Cars Agent" → click "Review"
Review permissions → "Allow"
Check box next to your workspace
Click "Add To 1 Workspaces"
Select "Everyone"
Click "Save"
Step 2: Surface Agent in Slack
In Slack workspace, refresh (Ctrl/Cmd + R)
Look for Agentforce icon in left navigation
If not visible, check "Apps" section for "Koa Cars Agent"
Step 3: Pin to Top Bar
Click workspace name → Preferences → Navigation
Under "App agents & Assistants", check "Koa Cars Agent"
Agent now appears in top-right corner
Phase 6: Test Agent Functionality
Test 1: Create Customer Brief Canvas
Click Koa Cars Agent (top-right or left nav)
Type: Could you create a customer brief for Oldacres's Electra of Dallas and add that to a Canvas?
Agent creates canvas with customer info
Type: Can you elaborate the vehicle definition of all the vehicles owned by the customer and add it to the summary in the canvas?
If asked, respond: Yes
Review updated canvas
Test 2: Work with Service Appointments
Create channel: "service-interactions"
In channel settings, go to "Agents" tab
Add "Koa Cars Agent"
Test these interactions:
Conversation flow:

Wait for response showing work order

Wait for service appointment details

Should show current date (December 29, 2025)

Click "Confirm" button

Review status options

Click "Confirm" button

Step 3: Verify in Salesforce
Go back to Salesforce
Navigate to Service Appointments
Find the appointment for Oldacres's Electra of Dallas
Verify:
Due Date: January 4, 2026
Status: In Progress
Key Success Criteria:
✅ Slack sandbox provisioned and connected
✅ Salesforce-Slack connection active
✅ Koa Cars Agent created and activated
✅ Agent accessible in Slack (sidebar + top bar)
✅ Customer brief canvas created successfully
✅ Service appointment updated via Slack
✅ Changes reflected in Salesforce records

Troubleshooting Tips:
If agent doesn't appear in Slack:

Wait 2-3 minutes and refresh
Check Agentforce tab in Slack admin
Verify agent is activated in Salesforce
If connection fails:

Verify package installation completed
Check user has correct permissions
Re-approve connection in both systems
If agent can't find records:

Verify you're in correct org
Check user has access to Automotive Cloud records
Ensure Service Console app is accessible